solution: ```class Solution {
    public long maximumTripletValue(int[] nums) {
        long max = 0;
        int n = nums.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < n - 2; i++) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n - 1; j++) {
                long diff = nums[i] - nums[j];
                if (diff <= 0) continue;
                for (int k = j + 1; k < n; k++) {
                    long val = diff * nums[k];
                    if (val > max) max = val;
                }
            }
        }
        return max;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n^3)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Brute-force triple loop is acceptable because n ≤ 100. The innermost loop only executes when nums[i] > nums[j], pruning many cases.

